                \n {"practice":"6","code":"DM-4","subCode":"c)","explanation":"Deferring security-related issues requires a documented process to assess and justify postponement, including risk evaluation and future reapplication plans.","context":"In ICS environments, immediate resolution of security issues may not always be feasible due to operational constraints or resource limitations.","challenges":["Risk Assessment Accuracy: Ensuring deferred risks are accurately quantified (e.g., a vulnerability in a legacy PLC may be rated as low risk due to network segmentation but could escalate if segmentation fails).","Stakeholder Alignment: Gaining consensus on deferral decisions (e.g., operations teams may prioritize uptime over patching a non-critical vulnerability).","Documentation Gaps: Incomplete records of deferred issues (e.g., missing risk justification for a deferred firewall rule review).","Future Reapplication: Tracking and revisiting deferred items (e.g., a deferred patch for a Windows XP HMI may be forgotten).","Regulatory Compliance: Demonstrating due diligence to auditors (e.g., explaining why a vulnerability in an OT system was deferred for 12 months)."],"best_practices":[{"description":"Implement a risk register with deferred items, including risk scores, mitigation controls, and review dates (e.g., using a spreadsheet or GRC tool).","url":"https://www.sans.org/white-papers/36280/","url_description":"SANS guide on OT risk registers, aligned with IEC 62443-4-1 deferred risk management."},{"description":"Conduct quarterly reviews of deferred issues with cross-functional teams (e.g., IT/OT security and operations).","url":"https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/Defending_OT_508c.pdf","url_description":"CISA's OT defense guide emphasizing periodic risk reassessment."},{"description":"Use compensating controls for deferred risks (e.g., network micro-segmentation for an unpatched ICS device).","url":"https://www.se.com/ww/en/work/solutions/syst